// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// T119 — non-default config: `indent = "tab"` emits a literal `\t`
// at every indent level (rather than spaces). The struct shape is
// the simplest body that exercises an indented context — its
// members live inside a `Doc::nest(indentStep(), ...)` so a config
// that maps `indent` → tab flows through the existing
// `LayoutPlanner::indentStep()` helper into the renderer's
// `emitIndent` machinery.
//
// `LayoutPlanner::indentStep()` returns 1 for `Indent::Tab`; the
// renderer's `emitIndent` checks `columnIndent > 0` and emits a
// single `\t` regardless of count, so the per-line prefix is
// exactly one tab character.

// RUN: rm -rf %t.tab && mkdir -p %t.tab
// RUN: printf 'indent = "tab"\n' > %t.tab/.nsl-fmt.toml
// RUN: printf 'struct s { aaa[8]; bb[16]; };\n' > %t.tab/s.nsl
// RUN: cd %t.tab && nsl-fmt s.nsl | FileCheck %s
//
// FileCheck patterns: each member line begins with a literal tab
// character, followed by the member name. Use `{{^	}}` to match
// the literal tab at start-of-line (FileCheck regex syntax).
//
// CHECK: struct s {
// CHECK-NEXT: {{^	aaa}}
// CHECK-NEXT: {{^	bb}}
// CHECK-NEXT: };
